13:
Me too...
It sounds like someone is playing a
violin!
18:
Why on earth would someone be
doing that?
29:
I see, it's almost as if she's casting a
spell through the violin itself.
41: She was all by herself, wasn't she?
45:
It looked that way. Given how she
dispatched those monsters,
perhaps she's used to moving
through the Kaleidoscope alone.
46:
So long as she stays away from the
depths, she should be fine.
49:
Yeah, you're right. She seemed quite
strong—those monsters just melted!
60:
That violinist from before? I can't
believe she went all the way to the
depths of the Kaleidoscope...
67: Don't move, all right? I'll go get help!
77:
I'm terribly sorry to cause you so
much trouble. Oh goodness...
81:
Don't worry about us! We're just glad
you're okay. How are you on food?
Do you want seconds?
83:
Gladly... It's been so long since I last
ate something this delicious. I've
mostly been getting by on
wildflowers and herbs for the past
couple days...
87:
I don't think I've ever tasted meat
this soft and juicy... I recognize the
flavor, but the preparation is
extraordinary. Did you cook this?
90:
Yes! I'm so glad you noticed.
Actually, I did a lot of research on
how to properly tenderize the meat
before—
96:
Hold on a moment! Can we leave
the culinary talk for later? We still
don't even know your name!
100:
I'm sorry, it completely slipped my
mind. My name is Lyra. Lyra
Ebelsorte.
104:
My name is Stella. I am the keeper of
Starview Village.
109:
It just occurred to me that I don't
know where I am. I was venturing
through the Kaleidoscope alone, but
I'm not sure what happened next.
115:
Well, that's gonna take some
explaining.
122:
I see... So I've ended up in a
completely different world. I heard
rumors of this, but I didn't think they
were true...
127:
Lyra, if you don't mind, could you tell
us why you were traveling through
Kaleidoscope entirely on your own?
130: Because I was told to do so.
138:
By a man who is... looking after me.
He runs a money-lending business.
141:
I'm terribly ashamed to even
mention it, but I've come into a
mountain of debt—left to me by my
parents, who suddenly disappeared.
146:
You were forced to become an
adventurer to repay your loan?
149:
That's correct. I didn't intend to get
myself injured like that. I really
should have been more careful in
the depths.
153:
Indeed, you should really be more
careful. Hmm... Regarding your debt,
I wonder if there's anything we could
do...
158:
Hey, there was that thing Lilie was
talking about the other day!
Remember?
161:
A consulting service for adventurers
who are down on their luck! She said
the guild started something like that
recently.
165:
You're right! Excellent memory,
Alk!
Let's not waste a single moment
and go talk to Pur Lilie!
177:
So it's THEM again, huh! They never
learn their lesson, do they...
181:
These moneylenders have caused
trouble in the past?
185:
"Caused trouble" isn't even the half
of it! They're a bunch of no-good
hawks profiting off novice
adventurers and refugees! Their
interest rates are criminal—literally!
186:
They've been exposed multiple
times, but that never stops them. I
can't believe they got to Lyra too!
192: Huh? Do you know each other?
195:
Alk, have you been living under a
rock?! That's Lyra—Palpebra's
biggest up-and-coming street
musician!
198:
Oh... I guess that somehow wasn't
on my radar.
204:
I do a few occasional performances
on the street—whenever my patron
demands me to. They're really
nothing special, though...
209:
Yes they ARE! You've got tons of fans
in this very guild, young lady!
212:
Still, I'm infuriated that our tips have
been going to those
money-grubbing crooks. I won't
stand for this!
219:
It seems like things have gotten
personal for Lilie...
224:
Heh, who knows... But now that she's
on the case, I have a feeling things
will work out just fine.
230: I... I don't know. I certainly hope so.
234:
Right, so, here's the scoop. We had a
look at the documents they
confiscated from you, and it turns
out the interest applied on your loan
was completely illegal!
237:
Which means... You don't have to
pay back a single penny
more—you're totally free of debt!
248:
I see. I suppose that means I can no
longer live in the accommodations
my patron was providing me... What
to do...
254:
You needn't worry—you can feel free
to come stay with us!
262: Of course. We welcome you, Lyra.
265:
Thank you so much, everyone. I'll try
not to be a burden.
268:
My name is Lyra Ebelsorte. My
specialties are adventuring,
housework...
270:
And... music!
Thank you for having me!
